      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Warding Flare\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"2\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Playerâ€™s Handbook (2014), p60\">Warding Flare</span></h3><p>Also at 1st level, you can interpose divine light between yourself and an attacking enemy. When you are attacked by a creature within 30 feet of you that you can see, you can use your reaction to impose disadvantage on the attack roll, causing light to flare before the attacker before it hits or misses. An attacker that can't be &amp;Reference[condition=blinded] is immune to this feature.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (a minimum of once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p></div></div>",
